        %h2 other groups
    .row
      .col-md-6
        %h3 fingerlings baby group
        %img{:src => '/images/photos/areas/fingerlings.jpg'}
        %p
          Our term time group for expectant mums and new babies meets on Wednesdays from 10 - 11.30am.
          Come for coffee and to chat about life with a baby ... and beyond!
        %p
          %a{:href => '#wv-find-us'} Call us for more information &raquo;
      .col-md-6
        %h3 big fish toddler group
        %img{:src => '/images/photos/areas/what-we-do/big-fish.jpg'}
        %p
          Our toddler group meets on Monday and Tuesday mornings during term time from 10am - 11:30am. There is plenty of room to play including an outside area, a large selection of toys and great cake! There's a waiting list for Monday's group but Tuesday's group is currently open to new members!
        %p
          %a{:href => '#wv-find-us'} Call us for more information &raquo;
    .row
      .col-md-6
        %h3 second sunday
        %p
          Students and 20's social events, meeting the second sunday of every month: we have regular film nights and spend plenty of time hanging out at the pub!
        %p
          %a{:href => '#wv-find-us'} Call us for more information &raquo;
      .col-md-6
        %h3 monday night football
        %p
          Come and play football every Monday evening 8-9pm at Knightwood Leisure Centre in Chandler's Ford. All abilities welcome.
        %p
          %a{:href => '#wv-find-us'} Call us for more information &raquo;
%section#wv-growing
  .shadow
  .container.wv-caption
    .row
      .col-md-12
        %h1 growing
        %p When we follow Jesus, our lives begin to change. As we grow in our faith, we may find we need to deal with the effects of the past - either things we've done which we wished we hadn’t, or things we've experienced through circumstances or relationships. God loves us and wants us to be free from the things that hold us back.
        %p Life groups and Sunday morning services are a great place to be prayed for. If we want to go deeper there are a variety of different options which are collectively called Streams of Hope.
    .row
      .col-md-3
        %h3 first stop
        %p
          Not sure where to start? Contact us for a First Stop appointment to discuss how we can best move forward.
        %p
          %a{:href => 'mailto:enquiries@streamsofhope.org.uk'} Make an enquiry &raquo;
      .col-md-3
        %h3 sozo
        %p
          Sozo is a powerful yet gentle prayer session that aims to deal with the things that are stopping us from connecting deeply with God.
        %p
          %a{:href => 'mailto:enquiries@streamsofhope.org.uk'} Make an enquiry &raquo;
      .col-md-3
        %h3 freedom in christ
        %p
          Freedom in Christ is a discipleship course that shows us who we are in Christ and how to live this out in day to day life.
        %p
          %a{:href => 'mailto:hello@winvin.org.uk?subject=Freedom+In+Christ'} Register your interest &raquo;
      .col-md-3
        %h3 love after marriage
        %p
          This course takes an in-depth look at relationships. It can revive and refresh your marriage, or help repair marriages that are struggling.
        %p
          %a{:href => 'mailto:hello@winvin.org.uk?subject=Love+after+marriage=enquiry'} Register your interest &raquo;
%section#wv-compassion
  .shadow
  .container
    .row
      .col-md-12
        %h1 compassion
        %p We live out our faith in Jesus by practically serving the needs of people in our city.
    .row
      .col-md-12
        %p Thank you so much for your generosity at Christmas giving toys and food to help those who needed them. Here are some comments from the agencies we work with:
        %p.quote "My client was feeling low and not looking forward to Christmas - it is such a sad and lonely time for them. The hamper lifted his spirits and he was so grateful for being thought of. It is such a pleasure to be able to nominate someone!"
        %p.quote "My client spent ages going through the box – loved the red tissue as an indication of being special. She looked through the items one by one, calling for her partner to see each and identifying a day on which to have what – to spread out the pleasure. Great joy from both!"
    .row
      .col-md-4
        %h3 children's storehouse
        %img{:src => '/images/photos/areas/what-we-do/store-house.jpg'}
        %p
          We provide free good quality childrens clothes and equipment to those in need. We run a voucher system and accept referrals from statutory organisations across the area. Please get in touch if you need our services or want to donate 'as new' goods.
        %p
          %a{:href => 'mailto:hello@winvin.org.uk?subject=Storehouse'} Get in touch &raquo;
      .col-md-4
        %h3 street team
        %img{:src => '/images/photos/areas/what-we-do/street-teams.jpg'}
        %p
          On Saturday nights, a team goes out into Winchester city centre with soup, rolls, tea, coffee, blankets, socks, hats and a listening ear. We help those on the streets by providing for basic needs and giving them someone to talk to.
        %p
          %a{:href => 'mailto:hello@winvin.org.uk?subject=Street teams enquiry'} Get involved &raquo;
      .col-md-4
        %h3 foodstore
        %img{:src => '/images/photos/areas/what-we-do/foodstore.jpg'}
        %p
          Foodstore reaches out to serve those in need by providing them with a simple bag of groceries.
        %p To get involved: "grab a bag, fill a bag, give a bag!" All you need to do is pick up a bag on a Sunday and bring it back full.
      .col-md-4
        %p
          %a{:href => 'https://s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/winchester-vineyard-website-assets/uploads/fs-full-list.pdf'} Download a shopping list &raquo;
    .row
      .col-md-4
        %h3 healing on the streets
        %img{:src => 'http://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/staticmap?center=51.062635, -1.311836&zoom=15&size=360x120&maptype=roadmap&markers=color:blue%7C51.062635,-1.311836&sensor=false'}
        %p
          Each Saturday afternoon we offer prayer for healing on the streets of Winchester. We meet on Kings Walk (near the Brooks shopping centre) from 2.30-4pm whatever the weather. This is a Winchester Churches Together initiative.
        %p
          %a{:href => 'http://winhealing.org.uk'} Visit the website &raquo;
      .col-md-4
        %h3 street pastors
        %img{:src => '/images/streetpastors.jpg'}
        %p
          We support the Winchester Street Pastors scheme, joining with other local churches to send trained teams onto the streets at night from 9:30pm to 3:30am. We support vulnerable individuals and provide practical help.
        %p
          %a{:href => 'http://winchester.streetpastors.org.uk'} Visit the website &raquo;
      .col-md-4
        %h3 karis kids
        %img{:src => '/images/kariskids.png'}
        %p
          Karis Kids is an initiative that integrates Ugandan children orphaned by AIDS into adoptive families. As a church we support the full time project leader, and we link families from church here with families in Uganda.
        %p
          %a{:href => 'http://kariskids.org.uk'} Visit the website &raquo;

